The studies were conducted across various countries and included people with SARS (13 studies), Ebola (1), MERS (3) and COVID-19 (38). Of the 55 articles, 53 were quantitative and 2 were qualitative. Details of the characteristics are listed in 
 Table 1 . Of the quantitative studies, fifty studies
 1-3, 14-58 incorporated validated questionnaires or measurement tools, while five (
 Bai et al., 2004; 
 Wong et al., 2005; 
 Khalid et al., 2016; 
 Chan et al., 2005; 
 Li et al., 2020c) used novel questionnaires.
